Meet <b>Shawn</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Shawn lives at <a href='/home/?user=omegashawn'>11646 Eagle Circle</a>, in the neighborhood of Westridge. He's only been a citizen of Millsberry for a short time, but has already proved himself to be a valuable member of the community!<br><br>In less than a month, he's not only received a trophy from the mayor for his efforts to help keep Peabody Park clean, but he's also gotten two from Coach Danner for his athletic achievements in Hop-N-Drop and Sink the Three.<br><br>Shawn is clearly very athletic, but he's also quite smart, too! He's very interested in astronomy and math, along with being very good with computers. He's already used his math skills to earn a trophy in Countdown! and he's also taken home a trophy from the astronomy-themed game Galactic Swirl Defender!<br><br>When he's not winning trophies, Shawn enjoys hanging out at the local card shop with his friends, or sitting around in the tree house that they recently build together. Shawn is also a very caring person, which makes him a great addition to Millsberry Academy.<br><br>On weekends, Shawn can often be spotted hanging out at the amusement park. After a fun day of going on rides and eating cotton candy, he likes to relax in his room and listen to country music.<br><br>Shawn is very excited about the recent snowfall, since all around his house one can find freshly-fallen snow with a beautiful light blue tint, which happens to be his favorite color.<br><br>If you haven't met Shawn already, be sure to stop by his house and pay this wonderful new citizen a visit! Congratulations, Shawn!</div>
